  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Wednesday. Today's disaster does not involve William at all, for once. This time, it is all Perry.",
      "zh": "星期三。今天的災難難得跟 William 完全無關，這次全是 Perry 惹的禍。"
    },
    {
      "en": "It started when Dad left the back door open for exactly four seconds to bring in the groceries.",
      "zh": "事情的起頭是爸爸為了搬進雜貨，把後門開了大概整整四秒鐘。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Four seconds was more than enough time for Perry to turn into a wild hunter chasing something only he could see.",
      "zh": "這四秒鐘對 Perry 來說已經綽綽有餘，足夠他變身成一位追逐著只有他看得見的獵物的野性獵人。"
    },
    {
      "en": "He shot out of the house like a furry rocket, tail wagging so fast it was basically a blur.",
      "zh": "他像一顆毛茸茸的火箭一樣衝出屋外，尾巴搖得飛快，幾乎只看得到一團殘影。"
    },
    {
      "en": "By the time we caught up, Perry had already dug three holes in Mom's garden, right next to the roots of her favorite tomato plant.",
      "zh": "等我們追上他的時候，Perry 已經在媽媽的花園裡挖了三個洞，就緊挨著她最愛的番茄植株的根部旁邊。"
    },
    {
      "en": "There was dark, wet soil all over his paws, his nose, and, somehow, one of his ears.",
      "zh": "他的爪子、鼻子，還有不知怎麼搞的其中一隻耳朵，全都沾滿了黑黑濕濕的泥土。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mom stood there, staring at her ruined garden, looking like she wanted to become a hunter herself, hunting one specific dog.",
      "zh": "媽媽站在那裡，盯著被破壞的花園，表情看起來自己也想變成一位獵人，專門獵捕一隻特定的狗。"
    },
    {
      "en": "But Perry was already gone again, this time knocking over the neighbor's trash can two houses down the block.",
      "zh": "但 Perry 早就又跑不見了，這次還撞倒了隔壁兩戶人家門口的垃圾桶。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Garbage went everywhere: banana peels, an old newspaper, and what looked like half a sandwich from three days ago.",
      "zh": "垃圾散落一地：香蕉皮、一份舊報紙，還有一個看起來是三天前吃剩的半份三明治。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William, of all people, was the one who finally caught him, holding a stick that Perry simply could not resist chasing.",
      "zh": "結果是 William，出乎意料地，最後拿著一根 Perry 完全無法抗拒的樹枝把他引了回來。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Every wild animal has a weakness,\" William announced proudly. \"Perry's weakness is sticks.\"",
      "zh": "William 得意地宣佈：「每個野生動物都有一個弱點，Perry 的弱點就是樹枝。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "It turns out my brother's endless knight games were finally good for something.",
      "zh": "結果我弟那些沒完沒了的騎士遊戲，總算派上了一次用場。"
    },
    {
      "en": "When we finally got Perry home, we noticed a small wound on his front paw, probably from a sharp rock or a broken bottle in that trash pile.",
      "zh": "把 Perry 帶回家之後，我們發現他前腳有一個小傷口，大概是垃圾堆裡一顆尖銳的石頭或破瓶子刺到的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Dad cleaned the wound carefully and said it was small, but we should keep an eye on it for a day or two.",
      "zh": "爸爸小心地清理了傷口，說傷勢不大，但我們這一兩天要多留意一下。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Perry, being the world's least dramatic hunter, did not seem bothered by the wound at all; he just wanted his dinner.",
      "zh": "Perry 這位全世界最不誇張的獵人，看起來完全不在意這個小傷口，他只想著要吃晚餐。"
    },
    {
      "en": "After dinner, Perry got a long overdue bath, and he shook water all over the bathroom, the hallway, and somehow my homework.",
      "zh": "晚餐後，Perry 洗了一個拖了很久的澡，牠把水甩得滿浴室、走廊都是，還不知怎麼甩到了我的作業上。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William brushed Perry's wet fur with an old comb while Perry sat there like a very patient, very confused king.",
      "zh": "William 用一把舊梳子幫 Perry 濕答答的毛梳理，Perry 就坐在那裡，像一位非常有耐心、又非常困惑的國王。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia came in to sweep up the mess and reminded us, once again, that dogs in her childhood lived outside and never caused this much trouble.",
      "zh": "Sophia 進來掃地收拾殘局，又一次提醒我們，她小時候的狗都住在戶外，從來不會惹出這麼多麻煩。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I reminded Sophia that her childhood dogs probably just had less exciting trash cans to explore.",
      "zh": "我提醒 Sophia，她小時候的狗大概只是沒有那麼精彩的垃圾桶可以探索而已。"
    },
    {
      "en": "By bedtime, Perry was clean, fed, and fast asleep, dreaming of whatever wild adventure he thinks he had today.",
      "zh": "到了睡覺時間，Perry 洗乾淨了、吃飽了，睡得香甜，夢裡大概還在回味他今天以為自己經歷的那場野性冒險。"
    },
    {
      "en": "We gave him one bone as a reward for finally coming home, even though nobody was quite sure he deserved a reward at all.",
      "zh": "我們給了他一根骨頭，獎勵他終於乖乖回家，雖然沒有人真的確定他配不配得到這個獎勵。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mom is already planning to buy a stronger lock for the back door, one that even a four-second gap cannot beat.",
      "zh": "媽媽已經在計劃買一個更堅固的後門鎖，一個連四秒鐘空檔都撐不過去的鎖。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Lesson of the day: never underestimate a dog with a small brain, a big appetite, and four free seconds.",
      "zh": "今日心得：永遠不要小看一隻腦子不大、食慾很大、又剛好有四秒鐘自由時間的狗。"
    }
  ],
